The paper discusses the acceleration of deep binary networks using modified von-Neumann machines, which falls under the category of computer architecture and digital circuits (cs.AR). The use of deep neural networks and machine learning techniques also suggests a possible sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of SRAM arrays and circuit techniques, which could fall under the sub-category of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper focuses on classification and recognition tasks, which could suggest a sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
